{
  "texts": [
    "They have been shown to achieve performance comparable to or even better than full-parameter fine-tuning while modifying only a small fraction of model parameters, thereby significantly lowering the barrier to model customization [130].",
    "Furthermore, studies indicate that well-optimized smaller models, such as those with 7B to 13B parameters, can rival the performance of much larger models on specific tasks.",
    "This offers a viable path for deploying LLM-based test generation in resource-constrained environments [108].Practical Constraints.",
    "The transition from academic research to industrial practice is also hindered by non-technical barriers, most notably data privacy and intellectual property issues [73,119,137].",
    "Many enterprises are reluctant to use commercial LLM APIs, as this entails sending proprietary source code to external servers for processing."
  ]
}